\u00e8re au nord de Toulouse : une ado de 15 ans tu\u00e9e, plusieurs personnes recherch\u00e9es|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2019/11/18/un-pont-suspendu-seffondre-dans-la-riviere-au-nord-de-toulouse,8547999.php|accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Highway A6 viaduct from Savona to Torino\n|[[Savona]]\n|[[Italy]]\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2019|November|24}}\n|Concrete bridge\n|heavy rain, landslide\n|0 dead, 0 injured\n|30 long highway bridge collapsed\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Another Bridge Collapse Highlights Italy's Infrastructure Crisis|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-24/viaduct-on-italy-s-a6-highway-collapses-during-landslide|accessdate=26 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Bridge near Aulla\n|[[Aulla]]\n|[[Italy]]\n|{{dts|format=dmy|202|April|08}}\n|Concrete bridge\n|\n|0 dead, 2 injured\n|260m long provincial road bridge collapsed\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Bridge on Genoa to Florence road collapses, two vehicles involved\n|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-bridge/bridge-on-italian-provincial-roadway-collapses-one-injured-idUSKBN21Q1E0|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Bridge disasters in fiction==\n* ''[[Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince]]'' (2005 novel): the fictional Brockdale Bridge, by the [[Death Eaters]] (replaced by the real-world [[Millennium Bridge, London]] in the [[Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince (film)|2009 film]])\n* ''[[Final Destination 5]]'' (2011), film\n* ''[[The Bridge over the River Kwai]]'' (1952 novel) and its 1957 film adaptation ''[[The Bridge on the River Kwai]]''\n* ''[[The Bridge of San Luis Rey]]'' (1927), novel\n* ''[[Ring of Fire (1961 film)|Ring of Fire]]'' (1961), film\n* ''[[The Cassandra Crossing]]'' (1976), film\n* ''[[The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly]]'' (1966), film (bridge intentionally destroyed by Blondie and Tuco)\n* ''[[The General (1926 film)]]''\n* ''[[P. T. Deutermann bibliography|Train Man]]'' (1999), novel featuring destruction of rail bridges over the [[Mississippi River]]\n* ''[[San Andreas (film)]]'' (2015), movie that portrays the destruction of several notable structures in the western United States, including the [[Golden Gate Bridge]], * ''[[San Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge]], [[Hoover Dam]] and the [[Pat Tillman Bridge]].\n* ''[[London Has Fallen]]'' (2016), film (bridges destroyed by terrorists)\n* ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'' (2018 episode), TV series (numerous bridges destroyed in Gotham)\n* ''[[A Single Shard]]'' (bridge railing breaks and causes Crane-man's death)\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Transport}}\n* {{Portal-inline|Engineering}}\n* [[List of dam failures]]\n* [[List of structural failures and collapses]]\n* [[List of accidents and disasters by death toll]]\n* [[List of road accidents]]\n* [[Lists of rail accidents]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.bridgeforum.com/dir/collapse/bridge/2004CAM1.html BridgeForum collapse database]\n\n{{Bridge footer}}\n{{Rail accidents}}\n{{Road accidents}}\n{{Disasters}}\n\n[[Category:Bridge disasters|*]]\n[[Category:Bridge maintenance]]\n[[Category:History of structural engineering]]\n[[Category:Lists of railway accidents and incidents]]\n[[Category:Lists of road transport incidents]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list of bridge failures'''.{{inc-transport|date=May 1976|Bridge=Hwy 75 SouthThe \"Template:Inc-transport\" template doesn't yet have a description, but there might be some information on the template's page.\nBridge\n Canadian River Bridge|Location=Calvin Oklahoma|Country=USA|Damage=Total Failure|Casulties=2 dead}}\n\n==Before 1800==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:94%;\"\n|-\n!Bridge\n!Location\n!Country\n!Date\n!Construction type, use of bridge\n!Reason\n!data-sort-type=\"number\" |Casualties\n!Damage\n!Comments\n|-\n|[[Ponte Milvio|Milvian<br />Bridge]]\n|[[Rome]]\n|Rome\n|{{dts|format=dmy|312|October|28}}\n|Wooden pontoon bridge replacing permanent stone b